title: For Sale:  1945 Colt 1911A1 .45ACP
postcontent:
According to online info, this pistol  was made in 1945. It does appear to have late war features such as :  Narrow checkered hammer, 7 groove Cyuga Motors mainspring housing and the Ordnance wheel and all proper markings. It has a Flannery WWII barrrel, and Late war plastic grips with proper part numbers. The entire pistol has been professionally refinished in the same Parco- Lubrite Maganese based parkerizing used by Colt near the end of the war. Blued M.S. Little WWII magazine. All parts have strong markings. I have filled most of the markings for the pictures. It is easily removed if you want. This pistol is a VERY nice example . Again, it has been refinished, but is priced accordingly. 1,138,000 was the end of Colt marking the slide with the same serial number as the slide.  This pistol was made after that so it would not have a matching number.
 Face to face in Oklahoma with OK driver's license. FFL required outside of Oklahoma. $35 covers transfer to your FFL and shipping.

title: For Sale:  460 ROWLAND 230 gr. HC-FN 1350fps / 931ft. lbs.
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=230


The 460 Rowland, as we load it, is squarely at mid 44 magnum power levels.  This means that a person can now carry a 1911 style combat pistol that has the power of a 44 mag. revolver, but is slimmer, faster to reload, faster to shoot and holds nine rounds instead of a revolver’s six.  The 460 Rowland casing is simply a 45 ACP case that has been slightly lengthened so it won’t chamber in a 45 ACP chamber.  It also has a stronger web area in the casing, so as to avoid "blow outs".

To acquire 460 Rowland test guns, I sent two of my 1911 45 acp pistols to Clark Custom Guns and had them install their 460 Rowland conversion kits. To date the converted 1911’s work great. I can fire a 255gr. hard cast bullet @ 1300 fps or a 230gr. FMJ-FN bullet @ 1350 fps. What a great "woods" pistol that still maintains combat pistol qualities.

We are using flash suppressed powders in each 460 Rowland load, so that if you have to shoot a bear or “bad guy” in the dark, the muzzle flash will not blind the shooter and we feel this feature is a big tactical advantage as most civilian shootings in America, occur in low light and we are willing to bet that most emergency wildlife shootings in the wilderness will be in low light too.

Note my real world velocities (below) from real world pistols, not laboratory test barrels.



Colt series 70 govt. mod. 5 inch with Clark 460 conversion

a)      1524 fps - 954 ft. lbs. - Item # 35A - 185gr. JHP

b)      1347 fps - 926 ft. lbs. -Item # 35B - 230gr. JHP

c)       1345 fps - 924 ft. lbs. - Item # 35C - 230gr. FMJ-FN

d)      1300 fps - 957 ft. lbs. - Item # 35D - 255gr. HC-FN



Colt 2009 circa Gold Cup govt. Mod. 5 inch with Clark 460 conversion

a)      1527 fps - 958 ft. lbs. - Item # 35A - 185gr. JHP

b)      1351 fps - 932 ft. lbs. - Item # 35B - 230gr. JHP

c)       1353 fps - 935 ft. lbs. - Item # 35C - 230gr. FMJ-FN

d)      1298 fps - 954 ft. lbs. - Item # 35D - 255gr. HC-FN



It should be noted that my 460 Rowland conversions are Clark Custom conversions. I did not try this ammunition in conversions manufactured by anyone other than Clark. This ammunition was reliable and safe in my test conversions, but I cannot verify the reliability or safety of this ammunition in conversions done by anyone other than Clark Custom.

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes Pensacola $75
postcontent:
The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 4 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes Pensacola $75
postcontent:
The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 4 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.

title: For Sale:  FN Five Seven 5.7 Double-Action Only (DAO) w/ AMMO
postcontent: This is an EXCELLENT CONDITION, Extremely RARE Original, FIRST variant, FN Five Seven 5.7 Double-Action Only (DAO) pistol, Imported year 2000. The FN Five-seven DAO pistols were not sold to the public!!! The first variant Five-seven DAO pistol was originally restricted by FN to law enforcement and military customers use ONLY. It is double-action only with a trigger pull of 4.5 to 6.5 daN (10 to 14 lbf) and NO manual safety device. It has a pebbled grip pattern, smoothly-contoured accessory rail, low profile fixed sights and a circular-shaped trigger guard designed to improve gloved use. It does not have a slide release and the slide is not serrated as on newer variants, but a portion of the slide is instead slightly concave to aid grasping. The original Five-seven pistols were shipped with only two (2) 20 round magazines. These mags will NOT work in later Five-seven IOM or USG variant unless the magazine safety has been removed or deactivated. This pistol comes in the original FNH hard case with operator’s instructions/manual, cleaning kit, and (2) 20 round magazines. PLUS ~ 500 rounds SS198LF LEO/Military Ammo (10 boxes).

title: For Sale:  FN Five Seven 5.7 Double-Action Only (DAO) w/ AMMO
postcontent: This is an EXCELLENT CONDITION, Extremely RARE Original, FIRST variant, FN Five Seven 5.7 Double-Action Only (DAO) pistol, Imported year 2000. The FN Five-seven DAO pistols were not sold to the public!!! The first variant Five-seven DAO pistol was originally restricted by FN to law enforcement and military customers use ONLY. It is double-action only with a trigger pull of 4.5 to 6.5 daN (10 to 14 lbf) and NO manual safety device. It has a pebbled grip pattern, smoothly-contoured accessory rail, low profile fixed sights and a circular-shaped trigger guard designed to improve gloved use. It does not have a slide release and the slide is not serrated as on newer variants, but a portion of the slide is instead slightly concave to aid grasping. The original Five-seven pistols were shipped with only two (2) 20 round magazines. These mags will NOT work in later Five-seven IOM or USG variant unless the magazine safety has been removed or deactivated. This pistol comes in the original FNH hard case with operator’s instructions/manual, cleaning kit, and (2) 20 round magazines. PLUS ~ 500 rounds SS198LF LEO/Military Ammo (10 boxes).

title: For Sale/Trade:  S&W Model 66 No Dash, SS, .357 Mag, 4" bbl
postcontent:
The “S&W Model 66 No Dash”, made between 1970 and 1977, was the second stainless handgun to be produced by S&W, and it was an immediate success.  The Model 60, introduced in 1965, was the first.

The first production run had stainless steel front and rear sights.  There were many customer complaints, because these sights “washed out” of view when acquiring targets in high light situations.  So early on, S&W first changed the rear sight to a blued/black one, but retained the stainless front sight.  That did not correct the entire problem, so the front sight was changed to a ramp with red insert during the second half of the production years --- Problem solved! 

*****This revolver is the completely corrected version.***** 

The last model of the “66” was the Model 66-7 which was discontinued in 2005.

The “66 No Dash” is much sought-after today by many collectors.  A lot of people say that if they could only have one revolver, the “66” would be it.

This weapon is in incredible condition for its age.  The round count is unknown, but it can’t be many.  The cylinder face is ultra-clean with no carbon residue, and the cylinder turning line is almost imperceptible.

The barrel is pinned, and the cylinder is recessed.

It is wearing brand-new Hogue Goncalo Alves (exotic wood) grips.  I’ll also include older S&W medallion K-Frame grips, but they are not original to this revolver.

No box or docs, just one fine handgun.  Now is your chance to own one of these rare iconic revolvers.
